<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNITA Attacks Market, Killing 18 in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The military men of the National
Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) killed 18
innocent civilians when they raided a market in Chipeta Town of
central Bie Province Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Kuito hospital in the provincial capital is full of people
who have been injured by the UNITA attack, the official Angola
News Agency Angog reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The market, about 30 kilometers southwest of Kuito, capital
city of Bie, is one built on some railway car storages.
</P>
<P>
Anastacia Nangueve, an old woman who survived the disaster with
only a bullet in her right knee, accused the UNITA men of firing
at people firstly in the market like mad and then looting almost
everything in the market.
</P>
<P>
People who fled from the town also charged that UNITA men were
taking youths by force to reinforce their army in Camacupa, a City
not very far from Chipeta, and that any one who dared to refuse or
intended to run away would be killed on the spot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
