<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Accuses Greece, Cyprus of Escalating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Turkey on Thursday accused Greece and
Cyprus of escalating the tensions in Cyprus and the Eastern
Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Foreign Ministry's deputy spokesman Sermet Atacanli
told reporters in Ankara that the ongoing flight of Greek fighter
jets over Cyprus shows that the Greek-Greek Cypriot front insists
on raising tension in the island.
</P>
<P>
Four Greek fighter jets on Wednesday attempted to land at a
military air base in Cyprus, but "had to turn back without
landing," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The jets were participating in military exercises by the Greek
Air Force near Cyprus, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Greek and Greek Cypriot provocations are deepening the
confidence rift and harming the stability on the island, " he said.
</P>
<P>
The landing of Greek F-16 fighter jets in a military air base
in Cyprus last spring led to a sharp escalation of tension in
relations between Turkey and Greece. Turkey retaliated by sending
F-16s to the Turkish Cypriot side on the island.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Greece, both NATO members, have long been at odds
over the limits of air space, sovereignty over some Aegean islands
and the Cyprus issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
