<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Injured in Bomb Blast in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- At least one person was injured, but
nobody was killed in the bomb blast which occurred in the biggest
market in Uganda' s capital city Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
The injured is a person who is a cleaner at the Owino market.
He was injured in the leg, Deputy Spokesman John Kimera told
Xinhua in the market this evening.
</P>
<P>
He said the bomb went off at around 7:40 p.m. when the market
was closing. People were moving out when the explosion was heard.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was not powerful, and the motorcycles and cars parked
nearby were not damaged, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, the Kafumbe road leading to the Owino market was
closed to traffic. Ballistic experts from the police are still
piecing up information to establish the type of the bomb.
</P>
<P>
Police officers are checking nearby hospitals to see if more
people were injured.
</P>
<P>
This is the fifth bomb blast which occurred this year and the
second one in this month. A grenade explosion last Saturday
injured at least five people drinking in a pub. Bomb blasts this
year have killed at least 10 people and injured dozens of others.
</P>
</TEXT>
