<HEADLINE> Rugova Says NATO Force in Kosovo Is Vital to Stop War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The top ethnic Albanian leader Ibrahim
Rugova said Thursday that the presence of an international peace
force in Kosovo which included NATO was a "key condition" to
solving the Balkan crisis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint press conference Thursday evening with
Italian Prime Minister Massimo D'Alema and Italian Foreign
Minister Lamberto Dini, Rugova said that the "installation of an
international peace keeping force composed of NATO and other
countries" was vital to stop the conflict over Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"The conditions for reaching a negotiated settlement are those
laid down by the international community," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that in order for Kosovar refugees to return home, the
withdrawal of Serbian troops and the creation of "secure
conditions" were necessary.
</P>
<P>
"I am for peace and non-violent resistance, and the entire
Kosovo population, including the Kosovo Liberation Army, is in
favor of a peaceful, political solution," he said.
</P>
<P>
D'Alema said that "Something is beginning to crack in the
marble-like position of Belgrade."
</P>
<P>
He told the Kosovar leader that "We will be at your side in the
search for a peaceful solution."
</P>
<P>
Dini, just back from a Group of Eight meeting in Bonn, also
said that there were "glimmers of hope" which hadn't existed
before, and that "We are getting closer to a solution."
</P>
<P>
He said that Belgrade had made "significant gestures" like that
of releasing the three U.S. soldiers captured by Serbia last month
and allowing Rugova to come to Rome.
</P>
<P>
He said that Thursday afternoon's G8 meeting had shown that not
only NATO but a "wider community" had "fixed principles" about the
conflict.
</P>
<P>
Rugova held talks with D'Alema and Dini Wednesday evening,
reviewing with the Italian leaders step-by-step developments of
the crisis in Kosovo. They also examined the possibilities for a
political-diplomatic solution to the ongoing conflict. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
