<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Sector Called to Join in Zambia's Hydro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has announced
a package of incentives for private sector participation in hydro
power generation and transmission.
</P>
<P>
The incentives comprise financial arrangements, fiscal
concessions, security and institutional arrangements.
</P>
<P>
Launching a document titled "framework and package of
incentives for private sector participation in hydro power
generation and transmission development", Energy and Water
Development Minister, Ben Mwila described the incentives as "a new
and unique policy."
</P>
<P>
The framework and package of incentives provided by the
government would give prospective investors sufficient confidence
and comfort, Mwila said in Lusaka Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The government has categorized projects for investment into
power generation and transmission.
</P>
<P>
Projects shall be offered to the private sector on the basis of
"build, operate and transfer" in case of power generation.
</P>
<P>
For transmission development, the offer is on the principle of
"build, own and maintain."
</P>
<P>
"For these projects government is offering internationally
competitive terms and simplification of procedures, by
establishing a one window operation," Mwila said.
</P>
<P>
The ownership of these power projects would be transferred to
the government or its appointed agent free of charge after 30
years of operation.
</P>
<P>
After 30 years of operation the government would lease out the
operation and maintenance of the plant, and other things being
equal to the original entrepreneurs, who would have the first
preference for continued operation and maintenance.
</P>
<P>
Fiscal incentives for investors include 10-year corporate tax
exemption, tax free importation of equipment for generation,
transmission and distribution of power, exemption from income tax
in Zambia for foreign lenders and free repatriation of equity
along with dividends.
</P>
<P>
The government is to create an office for promoting private
power investment within the ministry of Energy and Water
Development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
