<HEADLINE> Over 20,000 Meningitis Cases Registered in Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Sudan saw an outbreak of meningitis
with the total number of contractors hitting 21,337, of whom 1,513
died since the first week of last December.
</P>
<P>
Undersecretary of the Sudanese Health Ministry Prof. Bashir
Ibrahim told reporters that the recurrence rate of the epidemic
was low in the western Darfour province and high in other
provinces such as Khartoum.
</P>
<P>
Meningitis first showed up in the two provinces of the White
Nile and the Northern. And a medical team, including
representatives of the Dutch Embassy in Khartoum has been sent to
assess the situation in the two areas, said the official.
</P>
<P>
The World Health Organization has provided 3 million dosages of
meningitis vaccine to the affected-areas, Ibrahim added.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also trained medical personnel in the provinces of
the White River, Al-Gazira, Greater Kardafan, Sanar and the Blue
Nile.
</P>
<P>
The International Committee of the Red Cross appealed earlier
this week for providing vaccines to Sudan's highly-populated urban
and rural areas, saying that up to 20 million people in the
country were waiting for vaccination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
