<HEADLINE> France to Reinforce Air Force Engagement in Yugoslav War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 6 (Xinhua) -- France will increase by 25 percent its
air force engagement in the NATO operation against Yugoslavia, by
sending more Mirage fighters and a number of bombers to Italy.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman of the French Defense Ministry Jean-Francois
Bureau said on Thursday that defense minister Alain Richard will
announce the reinforcement on Friday.
</P>
<P>
France will also send more ground troops to the Balkans to join
a peacekeeping mission in case a political agreement on Kosovo is
reached, he said.
</P>
<P>
About 60 French warplanes are participating in the NATO
operation, their missions including reconnaissance, bombings, air
defense, in-flight oil supply, detection and air port command.
</P>
<P>
The French air force has been in charge of about 10 percent of
all the missions of the NATO forces since the war broke out.
</P>
