<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Greek archaeologists announced
Thursday that they had discovered a life-size statue of the
goddess of hunting, Artemis, near the archaeological site of Dion,
northern Greece.
</P>
<P>
The statue was discovered in the remains of a temple dedicated
to the goddess near the mouth of the Vafyra river in the
prefecture of Pieria, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA)
