<HEADLINE> Ethiopians With HIV Form National Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Persons with HIV, the virus that
causes the lethal AIDS disease, have set up a national association
in Ethiopia called "the dawn of hope", President of the
association Zewdu Getachew announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Zewdu said 61 people who carry the virus are currently members
of the association which envisages to raise public awareness on
HIV/AIDS and ensure continued assistance to HIV carriers in the
country, the Ethiopian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The association would also strive for the respect for the
rights of the victims to work and get medical services, among
others.
</P>
<P>
The association has already received encouraging assistance
from the Ethiopian government, U.N. agencies and non-governmental
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The president also announced that an advisory board made up of
health and social workers, media personnel and various other
experts has been set up.
</P>
<P>
Mesfin Araya, chairman of the advisory board, told the press
that the association would bridge the existing wide gap between
the society and persons with HIV.
</P>
<P>
There are an estimated 2.5 million people with HIV virus in
Ethiopia which has a total population of 60 million. 
</P>
