<HEADLINE> Generating Unit Goes into Operation in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 6 (Xinhua) -- A 35,000-kw generating unit became
operational today at the Feilaixia Hydroelectric Power Station,
the largest water-control project in south China's Guangdong
Province.
</P>
<P>
This is the first of four generating units of its kind the
power station will eventually have. It is also the highest-
capacity bulb tubular turbine generating unit in China so far.
</P>
<P>
The other three generating units will go into operation by
September this year. The power station is designed to generate 554
million kwh of electricity annually, according to a local source.
