<HEADLINE> Beirut to Host Arab Capital Markets Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The fifth annual Arab capital
markets conference is due to be held in Beirut on May 12, the
Orient radio reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is organized by the Arabic business magazine
"Al-Iktissad Wal Amal" in collaboration with the Central Bank of
Lebanon, the Association of Lebanese Banks and the International
Finance Corporation which is the World Bank's financial arm.
</P>
<P>
The three-day event will attract 500 participants from 21
countries. Arab countries to be represented at the meeting include
the Gulf states, Palestine, Yemen and Algeria.
</P>
<P>
Several prominent Arab ministers, officials and businessmen are
expected to attend the gathering.
</P>
<P>
Among them are Saudi Arabia's Minister of Petroleum and Mineral
Resources Ali Bin Ibrahim al-Naimi, United Arab Emirates Minister
of State for Financial and Industrial Affairs Mohammed Khalfan bin
Kharbash, Palestinian Finance Minister Mohammad Zuhdi Nashashibi.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will focus on capital markets reforms and
privatization drives, the development of oil production and
markets, and the future of investments in the Middle East and
North Africa.
</P>
<P>
The event will also see several workshops, staged by various
international firms such as the U.S. Citibank and France's bank
Paribas. 
</P>
