<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1430 GMT, May 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN -- Foreign ministers of the Group of Eight countries have
agreed on principles for a Kosovo settlement and will ask the
United Nations to endorse it, German Foreign Minister Joschka
Fischer said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The draft plan calls for the deployment of "effective
international civil and security presence" in Kosovo. (Bonn-Kosovo-
Peace Plan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- A total of 30 rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers
Party (PKK) were killed in operations launched by government
security forces in eastern Turkey, officials said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The military operations came one day after a large group of PKK
militants ambushed the security forces on duty in Yayladere town
of Bingol province, in which nine soldiers were killed and another
was wounded, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency quoted the
officials as saying. They added that the armed clashes between the
PKK and the Turkish security forces are continuing in the region.
(Turkey-PKK)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan on Thursday ruled out any change in its
position on the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) and
reiterated that it will sign the treaty keeping in view its
security concern and in a situation free of coercion.
</P>
<P>
"On the CEBT our position is well-known. There is no change in
that position," a spokesman for the Pakistani Foreign Office Tariq
Altaf said at weekly press briefing. "Our security compulsions are
essentially in the framework of India's huge military build-up
including its nuclear and missile arsenal and increasing asymmetry
in the conventional field," the spokesman stressed. (Pakistan-CTBT)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Britain said on Thursday that the Macedonian border
with the Yugoslav province of Kosovo is to be reopened.
</P>
<P>
"The border in Macedonia has been or is being reopened," Prime
Minister Tony Blair's spokesman told reporters. On Wednesday,
Macedonia closed its border with Yugoslavia, saying it could not
cope with the influx of more Kosovo refugees. The closure left at
least 3,000 people waiting on the Kosovo side of the border on
Thursday, according to a Reuters report. (Britain-Yugoslavia-
Macedonia) 
</P>
