<HEADLINE> HK Oil Smugglers Sentenced in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Two Hong Kong people who had
attempted to smuggle diesel oil into neighboring Guangdong
Province were each sentenced to one year's imprisonment and fined
120,000 yuan here today by the Guangzhou Intermediate People's
Court.
</P>
<P>
Cheung Kin-hai, captain of the "Lotus Mountain" tanker, which
is owned by Hong Kong's New World Shipping Co., and Chan Long-fei,
a crew member on the boat, were found guilty of smuggling 314.7
tons of diesel oil, from which they gained 58,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
They were caught by officers of the Panyu Customs in the
province, when the illegal transaction was being done, January 6.
The police confiscated the cargo and the illicit money.
</P>
<P>
A court source reported that the criminals would have evaded
112,000 yuan in tariffs, if the plot had been successful. The
special anti-smuggling squad was set up January 8, and this was
the first case it had handled.  
</P>
