<HEADLINE> Henman, Kuerten Advance at German Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Third-seeded Tim Henman of Britain
advanced to the quarter-finals of the German Open men's tennis
tournament in Hamburg, with a 6-4, 6-1 comfortable win over
Argentine Mariano Puerta on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The victory marked the personal best clay result this season
for Henman, whose serve-and-volley game is more suited to faster
surfaces rather than the slow Hamburg clay.
</P>
<P>
Eighth-seeded Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten used his powerful
backhand to dismiss the Rainer Schuettler of Germany 6-4, 6-3,
also making the last eight.
</P>
<P>
Local favorite Tommy Haas became the only German to advance to
the quarter-finals when he rallied to beat Spaniard Alberto
Berasategui 3-6, 6-1, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
French qualifier Arnaud di Pasquale edged Jiri Novak of the
Czech Republic 7-6 (8-6), 7-6 (7-4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
