<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Ties with Indonesia in Soccer International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The team of Hong Kong, China
managed a 1-1 tie with Indonesia by coming from a goal behind in a
three-team, warm-up soccer tournament here on Thursday for the
qualification of 2000 Sydney Olympics here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
After a goalless first half, the fast Indonesians, who won the
four-nation invitation in Malaysia days ago, opened the scoring in
the second half. But the fighting host then made hundreds of home
crowd comfort by slamming home an equalizer.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has never beaten the Indonesians for nearly ten years.
This tie made the two teams head-to-head record at four draws and
three wins in favor of the Indonesians.
</P>
<P>
The event organized by the Hong Kong Football Association, is
running in a round robin format.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, China beat Chinese Taipei 4-0 in the opener on
Tuesday. Indonesia is going to meet Chinese Taipei on Sunday.
</P>
