<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Namibian President Sam Nujoma will
pay an official visit to Egypt in a week at an invitation of
President Hosni Mubarak, an official announced here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma's upcoming visit will be the first of its kind by a
Namibian head of state, Egyptian Assistant Foreign Minister for
African Affairs Ibrahim Ali Hassan told reporters.
</P>
