<HEADLINE> NATO Must Stop Killing in Yugoslavia: Russian DM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian Defense Minister Igor
Sergeyev said on Thursday at Sevastopol, a port city in southern
Ukraine, that NATO must stop its killing in Yugoslavia before a
peaceful solution can be found over the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev, who went to Sevastopol to mark the 54th anniversary
of anti-fascist war, told reporters that the bombardment of
Yugoslavia had been doubled since NATO celebrated its 50th
anniversary in Washington on April 23.
</P>
<P>
Half of the targets were civilian structures, said the defense
minister.
</P>
<P>
There would be no progress in finding a solution to the current
conflict in Yugoslavia before NATO stopped its air strikes against
the Balkan country, he added.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev, who arrived in Ukraine on Wednesday, also exchanged
views with Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma over the current
situation in the Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine shared almost the same attitude toward the settlement
of the Yugoslav issue with Russia, Sergeyev said. 
