<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO Air Strikes Create Ecological Catastrophe in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 6 (Xinhua) -- An open letter from Belgrade
said that the NATO air strikes, which has entered its seventh week
Thursday, has created "irrecoverable" ecological catastrophe in
Yugoslavia in addition to the growing death tolls of civilians.
</P>
<P>
The letter, distributed here on Thursday, is addressed to the
ministers of agriculture and specialized government agencies in
agricultural field by Nedelijko Sipovac, Yugoslav minister of
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
"By everyday planned bombing, NATO has caused ecological
catastrophe not only on the territory of FRY (the Federal Republic
of Yugoslavia), but on the territories of all Balkan, Danube
basin, Mediterranean and European countries as well," the letter
said.
</P>
<P>
"On a densely inhabited continent such as Europe is, where
ecological balance is rather sensitive, one of the basic world
postulates, the postulate of ecological right, proclaimed in Rio
de Janeiro in 1992, has been annulled," said the letter, made
public here via the Yugoslav Mission to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
"FRY has become one of the war polygons of NATO alliance, on
which are, unfortunately, being measured all technological war
accomplishments," the letter said.
</P>
<P>
"This is confirmed by the fact that on this country has been
launched 11,000 tons of most destructive explosive or in average
more than a kilogram per citizen, which equates to the destructive
power of about 9 atomic bombs launched on Hiroshima," Japan, the
letter said.
</P>
<P>
"Those damages are irrecoverable and those losses irreparable.
The biological diversity is not the property of the state or
nation on whose territory they can be found, and none of the
generations of humans have the exclusive right to enjoy them," the
letter said, "Such type of ecological losses affects THE WHOLE
REGION OR THE WHOLE OF THE THIRD WORLD."
</P>
<P>
Every country that bases its development on agriculture,
energetics and industry has on its territory stored smaller or
bigger quantities of materials that are aggressive to human health
or environment, the damage of which can cause extremely dangerous
consequences of wide range, the letter said.
</P>
<P>
"Despite all of this, NATO is carrying out planned bombing of
chemical plants intended for civil purposes, and bombing of
these is causing direct ecological catastrophe," the letter
said.
</P>
<P>
"By aiming at plants for production of artificial fertilizers
the complex increase of concentration of toxic material of
ammonia, chlorine and phosgene has been ascertained, and it is
well known that those were used as war gases during World War I,"
said the letter. "The result of those dangerous materials,
especially heavy metals, is also 'the black rain' that recently
fell over Pancevo, and which very soon will be falling over
Europe."
</P>
<P>
"The increased measured level of radioactivity is the result of
usages of bullets with impoverished uranium and it causes the
disastrous degradation of nature and seriously endangers the human
health of present and future generations," said the letter. "It
also causes the extreme ecological endangerment of living nature
and natural mechanisms for self protection and self generation."
</P>
<P>
"The damage caused to ozone layer will have strong consequences
to human kind, plant and animal world of the whole planet earth,
since it is well known that the damages do not occur only on the
area of activity," the letter said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
