<HEADLINE> LIFFE Trades 192BN Pounds Per Day In April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, MAY 6 (Xinhua) -- The nominal value of contracts traded
on the London International Financial Futures and Options Exchange
(LIFFE) averaged 192 billion pounds daily during April, down 14
percent in March.
</P>
<P>
Total outstanding business in all Euro money market contracts
at the end of April exceeded 2,300 billion euros, LIFFE announced
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Although April saw quieter trading conditions generally, open
interest in LIFFE's Three Month Euribor contracts has grown for
the fourth consecutive month, with a 14 percent increase over
March.
</P>
<P>
Hugh Freedberg, LIFFE's Chief Executive, said "LIFFE's share of
exchange-traded Euribor market volume remains at 87 percent."
</P>
<P>
"This shows that LIFFE continues to provide its customers with
the best market for euro-denominated money market products," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Open interest, a good indicator of liquidity and long-term use
of the market, stood at 6,510,795 contracts, valued at 2,738
billion pounds on 30 April 1999, LIFFE said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
