<HEADLINE> Romania's Government Decides to Impose Oil Embargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Government ruled in a
sitting on Thursday to impose the oil embargo on Yugoslavia, in
line with a European Union decision.
</P>
<P>
According to Adriana Saftoiu, spokeswoman of the cabinet, the
government bans the supply and the direct or indirect exportation
of oil and oil products from Romania to neighbouring Yugoslavia,
either by sea, land or air. Exempted from this decision are the
petroleum products bound for the Romanian diplomatic missions in
Yugoslavia, and the international peacekeeping forces and the
humanitarian relief organizations in the area, she added.
</P>
<P>
The decision will apply on Romania's entire territory and to
any individual or company who perform activities outside Romania.
Any violation of the decision carries administrative
responsibility, fines or penal sentences. 
</P>
</TEXT>
