<HEADLINE> Shanghai Industrial Sector Announces April Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's industrial sector
obtained a year-on-year increase of 12.2 percent in added value
which reached 15 billion yuan in April.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of industrial value added for the first four
months of the year stood at 51.6 billion yuan, growing at an
annual rate of 9.3 percent, according to the municipal statistics
bureau today.
</P>
<P>
The sales volume of industrial products sustained a growth
momentum since January, which amounted to 181.7 billion yuan for
the four-month period, up 7.9 percent from a year earlier. The
sales-to-output ratio in the January-April period climbed 0.7
percentage points on the corresponding period of last year to 96.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
The sector accumulated a total export volume of more than 30
billion yuan-worth during the first four months, while the deficit
of local state-owned firms dropped by 6.1 percent in the same
period.
</P>
<P>
The city's industrial sector also recorded a vigorous growth in
new products, which generated a total output value of 5.36 billion
yuan in April, a jump of 34 percent over the previous month.
</P>
</TEXT>
