<HEADLINE> Toxic Liquor Kills 20 in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 people have died and 25
others fallen sick in Bangladesh after drinking toxic liquor in
the northeastern district of Narsingdi, the official news agency
BSS reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Quoting police sources, the news agency said that about 45
people fell sick soon after taking rectified spirit from different
shops of the district town Thursday night.
</P>
