<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Parliament Approves Deployment of More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Bundestag, lower
parliamentary chamber, Friday in Bonn passed with overwhelming
majority a bill to deploy 1,000 more soldiers in Macedonia and
Albania.
</P>
<P>
Among the voting legislators, 566 were in favor with 43 against
and 7 abstained.
</P>
<P>
At present Germany has 3,300 soldiers stationed in Macedonia,
with further 850 to be deployed there in coming weeks. The
parliament bill will strengthen Germany's military presence in
Balkan region to over 5,000 soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Bonn's cabinet members said the additional troops would be
"strictly limited to" take part in humanitarian actions to help
the refugees in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Without military support, the humanitarian organizations can
not cope with the emergent situation in the region, said Foreign
Minister Joschka Fischer.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 parliamentary members from the Greens Party and
the Christian Democratic Union (CDU) said civil organizations
should play a more important role in helping the refugees.
</P>
<P>
Support from the military division will hurt the civil
character of humanitarian aid, the legislators said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
