<HEADLINE> International Presence in Kosovo Must Be Military: Chirac </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 7 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac said
on Friday that an international presence involved in peacekeeping
in Kosovo must be military.
</P>
<P>
Chirac pledged to specify the terms of the communique on
resolving the conflict issued by the G8 foreign ministers in Bonn
on Thursday. Chirac was speaking at a meeting with German
Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder and Polish President Aleksander
Kwasniewski in Nancy, eastern France.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that the ministers agreed that "an
efficient international civil and security force" organized by the
United Nations was necessary in Kosovo for guaranteeing the
security of the people.
</P>
<P>
"That means a military force, and everybody has understood it
well. It is a great success," he said. 
