<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Names Envoys for Balkans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 7 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Friday named Carl Bildt of Sweden and Eduard Kukan of
Slovakia as his envoys for the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
Carl Bildt, born in 1949, served as Prime Minister of Sweden
from 1991 to 1994. During the period, he negotiated the membership
of Sweden in the European Union.
</P>
