<HEADLINE> Vietnam Holds Grand Meeting to Mark Dien Bien Phu Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam held a grand meeting in Dien
Bien district of Vietnam's northwestern province Lai Chou Friday
to celebrate the 45th anniversary of the historic Dien Bien Phu
victory over the French army.
</P>
<P>
The Dien Bien Phu victory crowned the 1953-1954 Winter-Spring
strategic offensive of the Vietnamese people and army, changing
the war situation and creating decisive conditions for the success
of diplomatic initiatives in Geneva that led to the restoration of
peace in Indochina in 1954.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, according to a report of Vietnam News Agency
Friday, was attended by member of the Standing Committee of the
Politburo of the Communist Party of Vietnam Central Committee (CPV
CC) Pham The Duyet, CPV CC Politburo member and Vietnam's National
Defense Minister Pham Van Tra, representatives from Vietnam's
central party, government, and provincial and municipal agencies,
and the war veterans who took part in the Dien Bien Phu Campaign.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting, Pham The Duyet said the Dien Bien Phu
victory is an eloquent evidence of Vietnam's revolutionary
heroism.
</P>
<P>
He urged the Party Committee and people of Lai Chau to continue
to bring into full play the heroic tradition to turn the province
into a prosperous locality and join the rest of the country in the
current efforts for national industrialization and modernization.
</P>
<P>
The celebration ended with a parade to display the strength of
war veterans, armed forces and 21 ethnic minority groups living in
Lai Chau.  
</P>
</TEXT>
