<HEADLINE> SAARC Countries to Implement ISO-3720 Tea Specification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Members of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) agreed here Friday to
implement ISO-3720 tea specification at the point of sale.
</P>
<P>
At the end of a two-day SAARC convention on "Tea Cooperation"
Friday, SAARC tea producers also decided not to export inferior
quality tea to member countries.
</P>
<P>
To implement the ISO-3720 specification, member countries
decided to form a Tea Association of South Asia.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka Tea Board Chairman C. S. Raiwatte told the press that
the understanding on ISO-3720 by SAARC members would ensure that
cheap and inferior quality tea would not be exported.
</P>
<P>
SAARC members include Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Maldives,
Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka. 
</P>
