<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader on International Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar authorities published the
content of a recent interview by French reporter Delphine Evmoon
of Faits and Projets Magazine with Myanmar leader
Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar
State Peace and Development Council.
</P>
<P>
The official "Information Sheet", made available here Thursday,
carried the content of the interview.
</P>
<P>
Asked about Myanmar's foreign policy towards the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), Khin Nyunt said Myanmar joined
ASEAN with a view to promoting regional peace, stability and
prosperity through cooperation and integration with other nations
of the Southeast Asian region.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the policy towards China, he pointed out that China
is not only a neighboring country but also one of the most
important trading and economic partners of Myanmar, adding that
Myanmar looks forward to working together with both ASEAN and
China for mutual benefit in the interest of peace and progress.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the strong position of the United States and the
United Kingdom against Myanmar, he recalled that Myanmar had
maintained cordial relations with both of them previously, saying
that these relations cooled down since 1988.
</P>
<P>
He denied that it was Myanmar's doing since the country has
always desired good relations with them.
</P>
<P>
He said that Myanmar is fully aware of the importance of the
two countries in the world today, admitting that with their
cooperation in terms of development and technology, Myanmar shall
be able to march towards its goal for progress and modernization
at a much more rapid pace.
</P>
<P>
In view of this, he said, Myanmar has done its best to promote
good relations with these countries.
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately, he complained, the two countries have adopted a
very
negative attitude against Myanmar allegedly because of their
political
agenda.
</P>
<P>
Dealing with economic relations between France and Myanmar,
Khin Nyunt stated that the two countries have benefited from
fruitful cooperation in the economic sphere, while enjoying
friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar believes and hopes, he noted, that France will have a
better understanding and appreciation of the challenges Myanmar
faces and will work together with Myanmar in overcoming the
challenges.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar, he said, is satisfied with the progress of the
economic activities of the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
