<HEADLINE> Sun Jun Wins CBA MVP Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Sun Jun of Jilin Tigers won the
Most Valuable Player of the Year Award for the 1998-99 season
Chinese Basketball First Division League here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sun, whose team wrapped up the season ninth place, beat off
Wang Zhizhi from the title-winning August First by three votes.
Sun garnered 10 votes to Wang's seven in the voting participated
by managers from all the twelve first division sides.
</P>
<P>
The Tigers forward came in first both in the scoring and three-
pointer category, averaging 31.7 points and 4.4 three-pointer per
game. He placed the sixth in assists with an average of 3.7 per
game.
</P>
<P>
"I'm glad to receive the MVP Award," said Sun, member of the
Chinese national side which won eighth place in the Atlanta
Olympics. "But what really counts for me is that my team continues
to stay up in the top flight."
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhizhi, who ranked first in blocked shots and third in
scoring, shrugged off being upstaged by Sun, saying: "It doesn't
matter, really. I still have the chance to win the Award and I
believe I can do it next season."
</P>
<P>
Hu Weidong of Jiangsu won the prestigious award in the Chinese
domestic basketball league for 1995-96 and 96-97 season, while
last season's trophy went to Gong Xiaobing of Shandong Flaming
Bulls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
