<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Urges NATO to Stop Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Srdja Bozovic, chairman of the
Republics Chamber of the Yugoslav parliament, on Friday said he
would write a letter to the European Commission, urging NATO to
stop the bombing against his country.
</P>
<P>
Bozovic, who is on a visit to Ukraine, said that he hoped
Ukrainian Supreme Council Chairman Alexandr Tkachenko would join
him in submitting the letter.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo crisis should be solved through peaceful means, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Bozovic also pointed out that NATO's attack on Yugoslavia from
March 24 had seriously violated the charter of the United Nations
and some elementary requirements of the international law. The
Yugoslav people had no choice but to defend their motherland.
</P>
<P>
NATO's military action, which came under the excuse of
preventing humanitarian disaster in Kosovo, had resulted in more
casualties of civilians and refugees, he said.
</P>
<P>
So far, NATO's bombing has killed 1,200 people, injured more
than 5,000 and damaged 25 bridges, 23 transmitters and over 50
industrial structures. In addition, more than 500,000 people lost
their jobs due to the air strikes, Bozovic said. 
</P>
