<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Foreign Currency Assets Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary Authority
announced here today that the official foreign currency assets of
Hong Kong were 89.5 billion U.S. dollars at the end of April 1999,
unchanged from the end-March position.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong remains the world's fourth largest holder of foreign
currency reserves after Japan, the Chinese mainland and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign currency assets of 89.5 billion U.S. dollars
represent over seven times the currency circulation or about 40
percent of Hong Kong dollar M3, one of the highest ratios in the
world.  
