<HEADLINE> Youngest Professor Vows to Develop Career in Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- "Even without the special professor
position, I will still return from the Founder Group to Beijing
University, and do some applied research for software management,"
said Yang Zhenkun, 33, Beijing University's youngest professor.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education promulgated a name-list of 73
professors eligible to receive a supplementary income last month,
and Professor Yang was the youngest one listed.
</P>
<P>
Yang led his colleagues in developing the Raster Image
Processor (RIP), which has made the Founder Group the world's
leader in image and language processing, and their RIP has become
the international standard for image and language processor
manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Yang entered the mathematics department of Beijing University
in 1984 and received his doctorate degree in 1993. He then spent
ten years at Beijing University, which is very rare among his
peers, and he is the only professor without the experience of
studying and working abroad.
</P>
<P>
"The 100,000 yuan supplemental a year for a professor is not
very large an amount of money. The position is a kind of honor. No
matter in China or overseas, if you can get suitable opportunity
and working condition, you will surely to achieve success," said
Yang.
</P>
<P>
"As a young man, I was fortunate enough for I have also got the
platform given by Beijing University to develop my talents, and
that is also the reason why I choose to stay in China," he said.
</P>
