<DOCNO> XIE19990507.0155 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 100 Million Land Mines Planted Around World: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, May 7 (Xinhua) -- There are more than 100 million
anti-personnel land mines planted around the world, a report of
the International Campaign to Ban Land Mines said.
</P>
<P>
The report entitled "Land Mine Monitor 1999" available here
Friday said that at least 108 countries are stocking some 250
million anti-personnel land mines.
</P>
<P>
However, the reported noted that more than 30 countries have
removed and destroyed 12 million such mines while 12 countries
have totally destroyed their land mine stocks.
</P>
<P>
From 1993 to 1998, 16 countries spent a total of 640 million
U.S. dollars in removing land mines, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Originally, 54 countries produced land mines. Now, eight of
the 12 big producers have signed on the Ottawa convention on
banning the use, stock, production and transfer of anti-personnel
land mines, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The production of land mines has greatly decreased, it said,
citing that in the 15 years before 1993, 65 million land mines
were planted, which means four million each year, while in the
mid-1990s, only 2.5 million land mines were planted each year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
