The CPAA Cultural Entertainment Company, the marketing
organizer for the performance, said that it will bring many young
and promising performers into the limelight.
</P>
<P>
Several word-renowned performing groups have invited Chinese
award-winners to join them in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Pan also underscored that the upcoming performance is one fruit
of the educational and structural reforms that have been carried
out within the academies. The 30 arts academies and schools in
China boast 13,000 teachers and more than 100,000 students.
</P>
<P>
State authorities this year decided to thoroughly restructure
the arts academies, and raised the average annual tuition fee to
10,000 yuan (1,200 U.S. dollars). However, youngsters dreaming of
stardom still strive to obtain a quality education there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
