<HEADLINE> Earthquake Death Toll in Iran Reaches 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The death toll in the two strong
earthquakes in southern Iran has reached 20 and the number of the
injured reached 80 by Friday noon, Tehran radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The quakes measuring at 6.8 and 5.9 degrees at the open-ended
Richter scale rocked villages 50 kilometers south of Shiraz, the
Far province Friday morning at 3:30, 3:41 am local time (2300 and
2311 GMT Thursday) respectively.
</P>
<P>
Head of the natural disaster headquarters in Far province
Hassan Momtahen told the Islamic Republic News Agency that some
40 aftershocks jolted the region on Friday and eight of them were
measured between 4.0 and 4.5 degrees.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the villages of Richi, Chenar Faryab,
Karabas and Famur in the region, with a total of 600 families,
suffered 40 to 100 percent damages in the earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
The Geophysics Institute of Tehran University registered the
epicenter of the quakes at the Richi village, 50 kilometers south
of Shiraz, the capital of Far province.
</P>
<P>
Relief teams, rushing to the scene soon after the quakes, are
continuing to search for victims, reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
