<HEADLINE> Environmental Protection Depends on Upgrading of Engine Fuels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The two-day Conference on Clean Fuel
&AMP; Environment and Future Directions of Automotive Lubricants
Preliminary Agenda came to a close here today.
</P>
<P>
The upgrading of engine fuels and environmental protection in
China were discussed at the conference.
</P>
<P>
Effectively controlling air pollution has currently been
considered as an important factor to improve air quality and
guarantee people's health, said Tang Dagang, a director of the
Chinese Research Academy of Environment Sciences. He gave an
analysis of China's current air pollution situation at the
conference.
</P>
<P>
Hong Dingyi, director of the Technology Development Center of
China Petrochemical Corporation, pointed out that only by
constantly developing new technologies to produce low-cost clean
engine oil can refineries meet the requirements for the
development of the domestic automobile industry and environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
He said once the revised gasoline and diesel specifications are
officially implemented on July 1 this year, more vehicles will be
required to use unleaded gasoline.
</P>
<P>
The US-based Lubrizol Corporation, the world's largest producer
and supplier of additives for lubricants and fuels, gave a
detailed introduction of the trends and developments of worldwide
automobiles, engine fuels, lubricants and additives.
</P>
<P>
The conference was jointly staged by China's Society of
Automotive Engines, the Petroleum Refining Society of CPS (China
Petroleum Society) and Lubrizol.
</P>
<P>
This was the first joint conference between Lubrizol and the
Chinese organisations. 
</P>
