<HEADLINE> Urban Pollution Index in Northern China Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The urban pollution index of a
number of cities in north China climbed up due to weak winds over
the past week, according to a report released by the China
Environmental Monitoring Center here today.
</P>
<P>
However, the air quality turned better toward the end of the
week, the report said.
</P>
<P>
From April 30 to May 6, the cities of Shenzhen, Haikou,
Zhanjiang, Xiamen, Beihai, Hefei, Fuzhou, Ningbo, Shantou and
Guilin enjoyed excellent air quality, while 20 other cities,
including Guangzhou and Nanjing, reported good air quality.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Shanghai and 12 other cities reported slight air
pollution during the period. Lanzhou and Xining reported serious
air pollution, although their pollution indices were lower than
those of the previous week.  
</P>
