<HEADLINE> S. Leone Rebel Leader, ECOMOG Agree on Key </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leonean rebel leader Foday
Sankoh and the commander of the west African peace-keeping force
ECOMOG have agreed on a key condition for a cease-fire, Nigeria's
The Post Express newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sankoh agreed that his Revolutionary United Front (RUF) would
"free up main highways", a key condition of a cease-fire, Togolese
President Gnassingbe Eyadema disclosed following a meeting with
the Sierra Leonean rebel leader and ECOMOG Commander General Felix
Mujakeruo in Lome Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The government of President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah this week asked
the rebels to demonstrate their genuine desire for a cease-fire by
withdrawing from highways and the mainstay mining areas in the
west African country.
</P>
<P>
Sankoh and Mujakperuo "embraced each another and then had
lunch," said Eyadema, Chairman of the Economic Community of West
African States (ECOWAS), which along with the United Nations, is
arranging peace talks between the Kabbah government and the
rebels.
</P>
<P>
Sankoh and his field commanders have been meeting in Togolese
capital Lome since late last month to consult on strategy of
ending the eight-year conflict in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The rebels said they would produce a document outlining their
proposals at the weekend, and then hand it over to Togolese
authorities next Monday.
</P>
<P>
The head of a Sierra Leonean government delegation will then be
invited to Lome for peace talks with the rebels, a Togolese
official said, although no date was set for the possible meeting.
</P>
<P>
Sankoh who was sentenced to death for treason last October was
released temporarily from prison nearly three weeks ago to meet
face-to-face with his followers in Togo for the first time in two
years after being arrested in Nigeria on arms charges.
</P>
<P>
The RUF launched its guerrilla war in 1991. Since then, more
than 20, 000 people have died and half of the country's population
has been uprooted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
