<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices plunged Friday on the
Singapore Stock Market surrendering the bulk of this week's gains
and starting a heavy correction after weeks of strong rally.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index sank 75.19 points to 1899.45
points falling through the 1900 mark.
</P>
<P>
Turnover totaled 977.83 million shares valued at 1401.72
million Singapore dollars (about 824.30 million U.S. dollars).
Losers nearly ten times the gainers by 330 to 37 with 74 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Allgreen, the newly-listed property developer, topped the most
actives chart with a turnover of 149,09 million stocks. FCC was
the second on the volume list with a volume of 63.40 million
units. Econ Int was the next which saw 36.69 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SembLog was the top mover of the day rising 18 cents to 4.40
Singapore dollars. LiangCt edged up 11.5 cents to end at 1.02
Singapore dollars. Wee Poh inched up 7.5 cents to close at 0.445
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Bukit Sem led the losers of the day plummeting
150 cents to close at 19.00 Singapore dollars. SPH lost 140 cents
to end at 24.40 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 finished down 130 cents
to 24.20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted that Friday's sharpest one-day fall was largely
prompted by profit-taking on blue chips. 
</P>
