<DOCNO> XIE19990507.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Province Uses More Funds for Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
has attracted a total of three billion yuan (about 360 million U.S.
dollars) from at home and abroad in the past five years for
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Henan in the upper reaches of the Huaihe River is a major coal
producer in China. Therefore, it shoulders a heavy burden of
environmental protection. The Yima Gas Project and the
technological upgrading project of the province's papermaking
companies have used a total of over 60 million U.S. dollars, and
the harnessing project of the Huaihe River has consumed about 100
million U.S. dollars from Japan.
</P>
<P>
The province was provided with 1.17 billion yuan last year by
the central government for 19 infrastructure projects. And a loan
with a discount interest of 145 million yuan, an allocation of 206
million yuan from the National Development Bank, and a specific
fund of 10 million yuan from the central government have solved
the problem of drinking water for 700,000 residents along the
seriously-polluted Huaihe River.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the province has also intensified its cooperation and
technological exchanges with foreign countries in environmental
protection, including Japan, the United States and Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
