<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Police in Malaysia's southern
state of Johor seized 7.9 kilograms of heroin from a car Thursday,
the biggest seizure in the state so far this year, the Malaysian
national news agency Bernama reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, police checked a car driven by a
30-year-old man and found 17 packets of the heroin hidden in its
bonnet, Bernama said quoting Johor state Narcotics Department
Assistant Commissioner Mohd Ali Mohd Yusof.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested three people including a woman aged between 26
and 43 later after questioning the man (car driver), the report
said.
</P>
<P>
All of them would be charged under Section 39B of the Dangerous
Drugs Act which provides for the mandatory death sentence by
hanging on conviction, it said.
</P>
<P>
According to Mohd Ali, the seizure had a street value of 1.7
million ringgit (about 0.447 million U.S. dollars). 
