<HEADLINE> Tanzania Lifts Ban on Beauty Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has lifted a
half-year-old ban on holding Miss Tanzania contests, local media
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education and Culture issued a document
Thursday, saying that the beauty contests will help design the
national dress as an identity as well as promote the use of the
Kiswahili language popular in east Africa.
</P>
<P>
The document lists a number of regulations that must be adhered
to by the organizers and the contestants, including stating the
kind of clothes to be worn by the contestants and the prizes.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary stage of the contests should be held in as many
parts of the country as possible at district, regional and
national levels so as to give the contests a national character
and image.
</P>
<P>
The government reiterates that Kiswahili should be given
prominence in the contests. However, other languages such as
English, French, Arabic and others can also be used.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the contests said that a new round of contests
for Miss Tanzania is expected to start next week. 
