<HEADLINE> Chinese Economic Crimes Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua)-- China dealt with 69,655 economic
crimes during the first quarter of this year, up 13.43 percent
over the same period last year, according to a report by the State
Administration for Industry and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
The crimes involve a value of 1.08 billion yuan. Crimes
involving values of more than 300,000 yuan registered a rise of
more than two fold.
</P>
<P>
However, crimes involving values of more than one million yuan
number 17, down 59 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The crimes are in the areas of smuggling, fraud, unfair
competition and the violation of consumers' rights and interests.
</P>
