<HEADLINE> Trinidad Downs South Africa in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, May 7 (Xinhua) -- World Cup bidders South Africa
suffered a surprise defeat in their Caribbean tour opener, losing
2-0 to Trinidad and Tobago in Port of Spain on Friday.
</P>
<P>
American-based strikers Mickey Trotmann and Stern John scored
goals in the 27th and 34th minute respectively to help the home
side see off South Africa, who is bidding to host the 2006 World
Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
South African captain Doctor Khumalo had a penalty saved by
Trinidad goalkeeper Ince after 71 minutes.
</P>
<P>
South Africa will play Jamaica in Kingston on Sunday for the
last of their two-match tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
