<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers on Friday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- One step was made on Thursday toward a possible solution to
the Kosovo crisis, as the principal members of NATO and Russia
agreed upon the main lines of a peace process which would
guarantee the deployment of an international force in Kosovo.
Russia made an important step by not presenting any pre-condition
for realizing a political solution.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The agreement reached on Thursday by the Group of Eight
countries on a political solution to Kosovo remains in the
darkness of serious divergence between the United States and
Russia. U.S. President Bill Clinton described the agreement as a
step forward, but said the NATO would continue aggressively the
airstrikes. Russia said a political solution is impossible unless
NATO stops bombing.
</P>
<P>
-- French Defense Minister Alain Richard submitted on Thursday
a series of secret reports on the actions of the Serb military in
Kosovo to the prosecutor of the International Tribunal on war
crimes in former Yugoslavia, Louise Arbour. The documents include
the photo copies taken in the air by French reconnaissance planes,
showing the detention of groups of Kosovo Albanian men by Serbian
forces in rural areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
