<HEADLINE> Sweden Welcomes G-8 Agreement on Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Sweden Friday welcomed the G-8
agreement reached Thursday by Russia and the Group of Seven
industrialized countries on a political settlement to the Kosovo
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Swedish Foreign Minister Anna Lindh said in a statement that
the agreement would "bring hope" to a political solution.
</P>
<P>
She hoped the U.N. Security Council would reach a consensus on
the issue as the move would enjoy "extensive international support.
"
</P>
<P>
At a meeting in Bonn on Thursday, Russian and G-7 foreign
ministers agreed on a seven-point plan that calls for a deployment
of "effective international civil and security presence" in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
It also calls for a U.N. interim administration for Kosovo and
self-rule, but rejects independence of the Yugoslav province.
</P>
</TEXT>
