<HEADLINE> Kim Dae-jung Expects Drastic Improvement in Inter-Korean Ties This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, May 7 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim Dae-jung
said Friday that he expects a drastic improvement in inter-Korean
relations this year.
</P>
<P>
"I will map out all measures with caution in the expectation
that there will be a drastic improvement in inter-Korean relations
this year," Kim told a press conference attended by more than 120
foreign journalists at the presidential palace Blue House.
</P>
<P>
Asked to give details of the predicted "dramatic improvement,"
Kim said he was unable to give specifics, but suggested it may
include the resumption of dialogue between Seoul and Pyongyang and
the holding of economic cooperation conferences.
</P>
<P>
Kim forecast an epoch-making development that may remove the
Cold War structure on the Korean peninsula as soon as
international suspicions about the Kumchang-ri site in the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) are cleared up and a
report by U.S. special envoy William Perry is made public.
</P>
<P>
A United States inspection team will go to the DPRK soon to
check the suspected underground nuclear facility in Kumchang-ri.
</P>
</TEXT>
