<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing International Trade Fair Opens May 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- China's largest international trade
fair, the Beijing International Fair (BIF), will take place
between May 20 and 24 this year at the Beijing International
Exhibition Center, organizers announced here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,235 Chinese and overseas exhibitors will
participate in the fair, which has been held every two years since
1989, organizers announced at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Participants are from Australia, Austria, Bulgaria, Canada,
China, Czech, Egypt, France, Germany, Greece, Japan, Italy,
Lithuania, Poland, the Republic of Korea, Romania, Singapore,
Turkey, Yugoslavia, the United Kingdom, the United States, and
China's Hong Kong Special Administrative Region and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Commodities on display will include machinery, transport
equipment, electronics technology, telecommunications equipment,
light industry products, agricultural products, foodstuffs,
computers, clothing, silk, electric appliances, stone materials,
new technology, jewelry, and arts and crafts.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade (CCPIT), the upcoming fair will for the first
time include a section on sustainable growth. This section will
showcase a dozen pilot sustainable development zones in China, and
technology and products related to environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the exhibition will include a section for name
brand products, in a bid to help them expand their markets at home
and abroad, organizers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
