<HEADLINE> S. Africa Continues Peace Effort on DRC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The South African government
continued its diplomatic efforts to bring peace to the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRC) as Deputy President Thabo Mbeki met his
Rwandan counterpart, Paul Kagame, to discuss the DRC issue
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki's office gave no details of the discussion, except
confirming that it was part of the effort to bring pace to the
DRC.
</P>
<P>
Pretoria regards Kagame, who doubles defense minister, and
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe as the two key figures in the
DRC peace effort as Rwanda is allegedly providing the backbone of
the rebel forces fighting to overthrow DRC President Laurent
Kabila. Zimbabwe sent troops to fight along with the DRC
government forces last August soon after the rebels took up arms
against Kabila. 
</P>
