<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Market Bomb Blast Kills One, Injures 10 in Ugandan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and 10 others
injured in the early morning bomb blast at Natete Market in
Ugandan capital Kampala Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sulaiman Mulindwa, an eyewitness, told Xinhua at the market
Friday morning that the bomb went off at around 6:10 a.m. when
vendors were off- loading stuff from vehicles.
</P>
<P>
"Soon after the blast, someone called in the ambulances and
took the injured people to hospitals," he said.
</P>
<P>
The market in the suburb of Rubaga division, five kilometers
southwest of the downtown area, usually opens for business at 7:00
a.m. and there are crowds of vendors waiting for the gate of the
market to open at that time, he added.
</P>
<P>
The eyewitness said that the killed is a man who was taking a
bag of maize on his back when the bomb exploded underfoot. The
man died on the spot.
</P>
<P>
Among the injured was a tax collector, the eyewitness added.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate official comment on the incident.
</P>
<P>
This is the second bombing that occurred here within 12 hours.
A bomb went off at round 7:40 p.m. Thursday near a police post at
Owino market in downtown area, injuring at least one person.
</P>
<P>
There are altogether more than 50 people killed and over 180
injured in bomb blasts in the capital city since 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
