<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Recall Idle Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- China will impose a levy on land
which is planned to be used for construction but still remains
idle and it may even be taken under government control.
</P>
<P>
An senior official with Ministry of Land and Resources MLR)
said that the move is aimed at protecting arable land and curbing
random investment in real estate.
</P>
<P>
He said that idle land refers to land intended for construction
purposes but remains undeveloped beyond the deadline set by the
government.
</P>
<P>
According to a nationwide land survey two years ago, the
acreage of unused land hit 116,400 hectares, of the total, 55
percent of the 62,800 hectares of cultivated land were completely
destroyed and can not be reclaimed.
</P>
<P>
To change the situation, MLR recently issued Ways of Handling
Idle Land, which sets specific conditions on how to take over and
collect fees from idle land.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
