(PRIC) to integrate the country's different pension and retirement
fund systems, the Philippines News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Estrada was quoted as saying there is a need to integrate the
various pension and retirement fund systems to make them "more
equitable, efficient, affordable and financially sound."
</P>
<P>
He said the PRIC will review operations of the current
Philippine retirement income system so it can make recommendations
for reform and improvement, which will result in better service to
the people.
</P>
<P>
The 15-member PRIC will be composed of representatives from
the government, the armed forces, labor and the private sector,
the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The PRIC will assess operations of the current retirement
income system with focus on coverage of its major components, it
said.
</P>
<P>
It will also develop a shared vision of the basic scope and
structure of the retirement income system. 
