<HEADLINE> China's Petroleum Quality Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- A recent sample test indicates that
home-produced petroleum products are 100 percent qualified.
</P>
<P>
The test, conducted by State Bureau of Quality and Technical
Supervision, involved 20 batches of petroleum products from 20
enterprises in 11 provinces and municipalities, including No.90
lead free petroleum and No. 93 lead free petroleum.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises involved in the test are mainly leading
petroleum producers, which have a lion's share of the domestic
market.
</P>
<P>
But experts warned that petroleum producers still face severe
challenges, as China is expected to issue new standards on the
quality of petroleum, which will set stricter limits on such
harmful elements as alkene and aromatic hydrocarbons contained in
petroleum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
