<DOCNO> XIE19990507.0262 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Aged People Play Active Role in Society (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Chengzhe, a retired senior
engineer of Shenyang Foundry Plant in northeast China's Liaoning
Province, has chosen a totally different alternative to his former
career: clearing garbage as a contribution to society.
</P>
<P>
On the road along the 22-kilometer Xinkai river across Shenyang
city, Zhang and other retired people clear garbage and trim grass,
and even extend their work to take in nearby residential quarters
and schools.
</P>
<P>
The 65-year old Zhang Chengzhe, once a national technology
innovator and model laborer, has been given an audience by the
country's top leaders.
</P>
<P>
His current work has also won him the respect and support of
society. Learning about his work from the media, more Shenyang
residents have joined his group to make their city clean.
</P>
<P>
"In fact, I already thought of making more contributions to
society before my retirement," said Zhang. He and dozens of other
model laborers set up a real estate company to provide more
convenient services to citizens.
</P>
<P>
Zhang and his colleague have been praised by China's elderly
people's organizations, and regarded as a model for other aged
people, because their work proves that "the elderly are still able
to contribute to society".
</P>
<P>
"With their rich work and life experience the elderly can still
make contributions to societies. They should not be excluded from
doing social work just because they have retired from their
occupations." Yu Guohou, vice-chairman of the China's Old
Population Association.
</P>
</TEXT>
