<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction on Macao Handover Site Starts Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Construction of an interim facility
for the ceremony marking the handover of Macao from Portugal to
China will break ground next week and will be completed in
November, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
The structure, with a floor space of 6,000 sq m and a height of
20 m, can hold 2,500 people. It includes a main hall, a guest
house, a media center and a number of other subsidiary facilities,
an official with the Preparation Office for the Handover Ceremony
said.
</P>
<P>
The building is located near the newly-completed Cultural
Center not far away from the Hong Kong-Macao Ferry Terminal and
will be designed to fix into the features of the environment, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Some of the existing facilities will be made use of for the
handover ceremony to reduce the level of demolition and avoid
construction repetition.
</P>
<P>
The structure will be built with sturdy and durable materials,
but not for permanent purposes, he said, adding that the site will
be turned into a park after the metal framework is removed
following the handover ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The top and some walls of the building will be built with
transparent materials.
</P>
<P>
Construction work is expected to end in October and interior
decoration will be completed in November, the official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
