<HEADLINE> Shanghai Benefits from Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
industrial and commercial city, has been benefiting from its
emerging stock market since it was established as one of the
country's two stock exchanges in 1991.
</P>
<P>
An official with the municipal government said the city has
listed 122 local companies which have raised more than 60 billion
yuan from both home and abroad, greatly easing Shanghai's
financial situation.
</P>
<P>
These companies, operating in accordance with international
practices, have played an exemplary role in the reform of state-
owned enterprises which is aimed at building a modern enterprise
system.
</P>
<P>
The stock market has also helped accelerate the development of
Shanghai's pillar industries: automobiles, pharmaceuticals, and
computers.
</P>
<P>
One of the listed companies, the Shanghai Automobile Co. Ltd.,
is co-funding a 1.52-billion-U.S.dollar joint venture, Shanghai
General Motors Corp., together with General Motors Corporation of
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Stock Exchange now has 486 listed companies with
total shares valued at 1.14 trillion yuan, accounting for 14
percent of the country's GDP.  
</P>
</TEXT>
