<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Shows Ascending Trend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Cypriot stock market's forceful
rise exhibited last week was extended into this trading week, a
weekly market review said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, issued by the Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corportion Limited (CISCO), said the CISCO All-Share Index
registered an all-time high of 636.0 points in the week.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index closed at 630.5 points Thursday, a
weekly improvement of 18.6 points or 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of transactions this week was 35.2 million
Cyprus pounds (70.4 million U.S. dollars), compared to 24 million
pounds (48 million dollars) the week before.
</P>
<P>
The average daily volume for this week was at 7.0 million
pounds (14.1 million dollars), from 4.8 million pounds (9.6
million dollars) the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The highest daily volume for the week was achieved Tuesday,
when 10.2 million pounds (20.4 million dollars) was traded,
compared to 6.3 million pounds (12.6 million dollars) the week
before. 
</P>
