<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Oneworld, the giant alliance of
five major airlines, is holding talks with the United Arab
Emirates Airline for the possible entry of it as a member, the
Gulf News daily reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"If it goes ahead, Emirates Airline will join a club which
includes five of the world's largest airlines," said the paper.
</P>
<P>
