for Middle East, North Africa and Central Asia, said they had been
discussing the membership issue with Emirates Airline for the past
five months.
</P>
<P>
"Should the proposed deal with Emirates Airline materialize,
the carrier would join the five-airline league composed of
American Airlines, British Airways, Canadian Airlines, Cathay
Pacific and Qantas," Rousham said.
</P>
<P>
Besides the Emirates Airline, they were also talking with three
major airlines in the Middle East, he added.
</P>
