<HEADLINE> 40 Aftershocks Rock South Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- About 40 aftershocks rocked southern
Iran on Friday after two strong earthquake measuring at 6.8 and
5.9 degrees at the open-ended Richter scale killed at least 16
people and injured 51 others.
</P>
<P>
Head of the natural disaster headquarters in Far province
Hassan Momtahen told the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) that
eight of the aftershocks were measured between 4.0 and 4.5
degrees.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the villages of Richi, Chenar Faryab,
Karabas and Famur in the region with 600 families received 40 to
100 percent damages in the earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
IRNA said that the Geophysics Institute of Tehran University
registered the epicenter of the quakes at 50 kilometers south of
Shiraz, the capital of Far province.
</P>
<P>
The quakes occurred at 0330, 0341 hours local times (2300 and
2311 GMT Thursday) respectively. IRNA reported the first quake at
6.5 degrees, but also said that the quake was recorded at 6.8
degrees by a seismographic center in Shiraz.
</P>
<P>
Relief teams have rushed to the scene soon after the quakes,
IRNA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
