<DOCNO> XIE19990507.0296 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Making Progress In Water-Efficient Irrigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Water-efficient irrigation
equipment built in China over the past three years can save 15
billion cubic meters of water annually.
</P>
<P>
The 25 billion yuan put into the sector during that period has
helped expand the acreage of water-efficient irrigation area by 5.
6 million hectares, according to the Ministry of Water resources.
</P>
<P>
China has an acute shortage of water resources. The water used
for irrigation accounts for more than 70 percent of water use, but
only 40 percent of the water is really used effectively. Since
1996, China has increased efforts to save water and has spread the
use of water-saving irrigation in 300 counties, increasing the
amount of land by more than 1.3 million hectares annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
