<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> May 4th Movement's Spirit Never Out-Of-Date, Chinese Scholars Say </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences (CASS) held a forum today to mark the 80th anniversary of
the May 4th Movement.
</P>
<P>
Scholars attending the forum said they agree that the spirit of
the Movement will never go out of style and that it will influence
young Chinese for generations.
</P>
<P>
On May 4th, 1919, several thousand students from Beijing
University and a dozen other colleges, universities and schools
gathered in Tian'anmen Square to demonstrate and demand that
China's sovereignty and rights be fully respected. The movement
was firmly supported across the country and grew into an anti-
imperialist and anti-feudal political and cultural movement.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Wenhong, an associate research fellow in world history,
said at the forum that the democratic and scientific spirit
represented by the movement can benefit the current socialist
market process because free and fair competition and a scientific
way of thinking are basic market demands.
</P>
<P>
He said that the May 4th Movement showed the noble spirit of
sacrificing oneself for the whole of society and the people and
that this sense of responsibility and noble spirit should be
carried on.
</P>
<P>
A 34-year old scholar, Zhang Ximing, said at the forum that the
tradition, patriotism, and scientific and democratic spirit of the
May 4th Movement will be a valuable inheritance for all young
Chinese, while Wang Luolin, a vice-president of CASS, told the
forum that the essence of the May 4th Movement is patriotism: "At
present, when the reforms and opening-up are at a crucial period,
the younger generation should stir up their enthusiasm for
patriotism to advance the socialist modernization process."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990507.0305 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 06:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquakes Rock Southern Iran, Killing 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Two strong earthquake measuring at
6.8 and 5.9 degrees at the open-ended Richter scale rocked
southern Iran southern city of Shiraz on Friday morning, killing at
least 16 people, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Agency reported that the Geophysics Institute of Tehran
University registered the epicenter of the quakes at 50
kilometers south of Shiraz, the capital of Far province.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, the quakes, the quakes occurred at
0330, 0341 hours local times (2300 and 2311 GMT Thursday)
respectively, also wounded at least 51 people and damage caused to
the region was not immediately known.
</P>
<P>
IRNA reported the first quake at 6.5 degrees, but also said
that the quake was recorded at 6.8 degrees by a seismographic
center in Shiraz.
</P>
<P>
Relief teams have rushed to the scene soon after the quakes,
IRNA said. 
</P>
