<HEADLINE> Kuwait Loans 12 Mln Dollars for S.Lankan Irrigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka will get a loan of 3.7
million dinars (12.05 million U.S. dollars) from the Kuwait Fund
for Arab Economic Development for an irrigation rehabilitation
project in the south, officials said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to boost agricultural production and raising
the standard of living of people in Liyangastota, Muruthawela and
Badagiriya in southern Sri Lanka through the rehabilitation of the
irrigation systems in these areas.
</P>
<P>
The rehabilitation of the irrigation networks will result in
11,200 hectares of agricultural land benefitting.
</P>
<P>
The project also includes strengthening the capabilities of
operation and maintenance of the irrigation systems through the
provision of training, machinery and equipment and other
facilities.
</P>
<P>
The loan, expected to cover about 70 percent of the total cost
of the project, has to be repaid in 25 years with a 6 year grace
period. It will bear an interest of 2 percent per annum and a
charge of 0.5 percent for meeting and implementation expenses.
</P>
<P>
The loan is the sixth provided by the Kuwait Fund for Arab
Economic Development which has granted a total of 29.28 million
Kuwait dinars (95.4 million dollars) to Sri Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
