<HEADLINE> More Money Invested in U.S. Net Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Internet-related companies in
the United States received a total of 2.1 billion U.S. dollars in
venture capital in the first quarter, a market research firm said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Investments in net firms represented 58 percent of all venture
capital investment in the past quarter, said San Francisco-based
VentureOne, which tracks the venture capital industry. Firms
involved in electronic commerce and business services accounted
for almost 22 percent of the money invested in Internet companies.
</P>
<P>
VentureOne said that total venture capital investment in the
United States reached 3.6 billion dollars in the first quarter, up
32 percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
According to VentureOne's earlier releases, venture capital
investments in the United States reached an all time high of 12.52
billion dollars in 1998. Information technology remained the
strongest component of investment growth, accounting for 62
percent of the dollars invested, raising 7.77 billion dollars in
more than 1,000 deals. Its strength was fueled largely by
investment in communications and information services companies,
the market research firm said.
</P>
<P>
Also in 1998, the U.S. initial public offerings (IPO) market
for venture-backed companies saw a total of 4.23 billion dollars
raised by the 77 public companies going public. Internet companies
led the pack accounting for over 30 percent of all venture-backed
companies going public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
