<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes 1,800 Kilos of Drug in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar authorities seized a total of
1,839 kilos of narcotic drugs including 123.38 kilos of heroin and
412.1 kilos of opium in the first quarter of this year, according
to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the authorities also confiscated 1.81
million tablets of amphetamine stimulants and destroyed 8 drug
refineries.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,550 drug offenders were also punished in
connection with 1,162 related cases, the statistics showed.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the authorities seized a total of 10,794 kilos of
drugs including 403.8 kilos of heroin and 5,393.6 kilos of opium
as well as 16.02 million tablets of stimulants.
</P>
<P>
During the year, a total of 4,845 drug offenders were punished
in connection with 3,546 related cases. 
</P>
