<HEADLINE> China to Introduce Project Appraisal System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- China is trying to improve its
project evaluation expertise by introducing a project selection
and appraisal system to avoid duplication of construction as well
as reducing investment risks, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
An international seminar on project analyses held on May 6 in
Beijing pioneered the move.
</P>
<P>
At the seminar Edward Merrow, president of the U.S-based
Independent Project Analysis Inc (IPA), pledged to bring the most
advanced project selection, development and execution practices to
China.
</P>
<P>
Merrow introduced approaches and systems known as PES and
benchmarking to participants at the seminar.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was sponsored by the China National Chemical
Construction Corp.(CNCCC) and Beijing Mairuo Industry Technical
Consulting Co Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Chen Lihua, president of CNCCC, said blind investment and
duplication of projects had caused overcapacity and affected
profitability.
</P>
<P>
"Project evaluation and scientific analysis are a very
important challenge for domestic enterprises seeking durable
profits," he said.
</P>
<P>
Many domestic enterprises, especially state-owned ones,
suffered losses upon completion of projects into which they had
injected huge amounts of fund.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed this to the lack of a standardized
feasibility studies and analysis prior to construction.
</P>
<P>
The central government is taking tough measures to overhaul the
management of some large state-owned enterprises and requiring
newly-appointed corporate leaders to take full responsibility for
the investment they make.
</P>
<P>
Meng Quansheng, director of the Planning and Development
Department of the State Administration of Petroleum and Chemical
Industries, said that reliable project evaluation and accurate
forecast are "absolutely indispensable" for the strengthening of
structural adjustment in the industry as well as improvement of
project management level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
