<HEADLINE> Central China's Hi-Tech Industry Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province has
a goal of helping its hi-tech industry increase output value to 10
percent of its GDP by next year and to as much as 15 percent by
2002.
</P>
<P>
According to the Provincial Planning Commission, Henan's hi-
tech industry is expected to generate 50 billion yuan in output
value by 2000 and 90 billion yuan by 2002. Priority will be given
to electronic information, bio-engineering, and new materials.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to help develop two hi-tech groups, each
with more than 5 billion yuan in annual output, 12 enterprises
each with more than a billion yuan in annual output, and 30 each
with more than 100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, the province had 1,065 types of hi-tech
products, 960 of which had been patented, and 150 of which were
selling abroad. 
</P>
