<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Balkans envoy Viktor
Chernomyrdin on Thursday urged the United Nations to play a
greater role in the efforts to settle the Yugoslav crisis and
added that Russia was ready to mediate.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Public Russian Television after a
telephone conversation with U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan,
Chernomyrdin said he sincerely hoped the United Nations would play
an active role in bringing the warring parties in the Kosovo
conflict to the negotiating table.
</P>
