<HEADLINE> U.S. House Approves 13.1 Billion U.S. Dollars for Kosovo War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. House of Representatives
on Thursday approved a 13.1 billion U.S. dollar package to pay for
the air war against Yugoslavia and increase the nation's military
readiness.
</P>
<P>
The move would more than double the six billion dollars
requested by President Bill Clinton last month to continue the war
until September and care for the refugees from Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Most of the bill will be paid for from this year's expected
federal surplus of 111 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Senate has not produced its own version of the legislation.
GOP leaders there have said they prefer a package closer in size
to Clinton's request.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that the House and Senate may reach a compromise
of about nine billion dollars next week. 
</P>
