<HEADLINE> South China City Attracts Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANYA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The city of Sanya in Hainan Province
has been attracting more and more overseas investors since last
year.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, some 597 overseas-funded enterprises have been
established in the city, involving investments of 1.2 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises have a total registered capital of 800
million U.S. dollars with investors from 23 countries or regions
worldwide including France, Japan, the United States, Hong Kong,
and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 28 overseas-funded companies registered in the city
with a total of 80 million U.S. dollars, five percent more than
the previous year.  
