<HEADLINE> Gigantic Oil Tanker Launched In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- A 71,000-dwt, double bottom, double
hull oil tanker has been launched in Shanghai, the largest of its
kind ever built in the country.
</P>
<P>
The tanker named "Emerald Sun" was built by Shanghai Hudong
Shipbuilding Group for a Singapore's tanker company.
</P>
<P>
The giant ship is 227 meters long, 32.26 meters wide and 20.2
meters tall and is designed to have 12.5 meters of draft.
</P>
<P>
The tanker's design meets the requirements of international
maritime regulations.
</P>
<P>
The Hudong Group has also built a 68,000-dwt similar tanker for
a Hong Kong client.  
