<DOCNO> XIE19990507.0386 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Credit to Assist Albania for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved a credit
of 30 million U.S. dollars for Albania to help the country counter
the economic effects of the crisis in neighboring Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The credit will provide quick-disbursing budget support to
allow the government of Albania to resume critical public
expenditures which were frozen to allow for the unbudgeted
expenditures incurred as a result of the massive inflow of
refugees since NATO launched airstrikes against Yugoslavia in
March 1999, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
It also will help alleviate the budgetary pressure as a
consequence of increased demands on the government and of revenue
losses which will result from the continuing crisis.
</P>
<P>
The bank said the project will safeguard Albania's functioning
public institutions during the period of crisis so that the
adopted reform agenda can be maintained, and help the government
maintain macroeconomic stabilization during a period where serious
shocks will affect orderly economic activities, put exceptional
demands on public expenditures, while reducing possibilities for
revenue collection.
</P>
<P>
The budget support provided by the credit will disburse through
the Public Expenditure Support Program set up in response to the
crisis.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided by the International Development
Association, a member of the World Bank, and will be payable in 40
years, including a 10-year grace period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
